def _unstack_multiple(data, clocs, fill_value=None):
    if len(clocs) == 0:
        return data

    # Get the MultiIndex
    index = data.index

    # Create lists of levels, codes, and names
    clevels = [index.levels[i] for i in clocs]
    ccodes = [index.codes[i] for i in clocs]
    cnames = [index.names[i] for i in clocs]
    
    # Perform unstack operation
    unstacked = data.unstack(clocs, fill_value=fill_value)

    # Modify the levels, codes, and names as needed based on the unstacked result
    
    # If unstacked result is a Series, update the index
    if isinstance(unstacked, Series):
        unstacked.index = MultiIndex.from_tuples(unstacked.index, names=cnames)
    # If unstacked result is a DataFrame, update the columns
    else:
        unstacked.columns = MultiIndex.from_tuples(unstacked.columns, names=cnames)

    return unstacked
